{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17496609","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17496609"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T08:52:02+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T08:52:02+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1396"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1396","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1396"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.62,0.29,0.02,0.04,0.03]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1396"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"54157"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1396","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1396"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1396"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"39629"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"2"},{"type":"tags","id":"11"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"28"},{"type":"tags","id":"31"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"160"},{"type":"tags","id":"489"},{"type":"tags","id":"1036"},{"type":"tags","id":"1114"},{"type":"tags","id":"1197"},{"type":"tags","id":"4174"},{"type":"tags","id":"4982"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"6610"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"657"},{"type":"contributions","id":"960"},{"type":"contributions","id":"13932"},{"type":"contributions","id":"40829"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42302"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43076"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"54157","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/54157"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 60-year-old woman presents to her general practitioner with sudden onset, sharp, right sided chest pain and shortness of breath. Her only medical history is metastatic melanoma, currently ceased intensive treatment and receiving community palliative care. On examination her pulse is 120min, blood pressure 110/90 mmHg, temperature 37.2\u00b0C, respiratory rate 30/min and SpO\u003Csub\u003E2\u003C/sub\u003E 93% on room air. Her chest is clear and there are no adventitious sounds, and her trachea is midline. She has a unilateral swelling in her left lower leg which is erythematous and tender. Her GP performs an an ECG.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following findings is most likely to be present on her ECG?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Sinus tachycardia","S1Q3T3 pattern","New Right Bundle Branch Block","Non-specific ST segment changes","Normal ECG"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis is a classical presentation of a pulmonary embolus (PE) causing pleuritic chest pain and shortness of breath, with a tachypnoea, on a background of lower limb DVT causing oedema and tenderness. An ECG should be performed when PE is suspected.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESinus tachycardia\u003C/strong\u003E is the most common abnormality seen in 40% of PE cases.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESigns of right ventricular strain (\u003Cstrong\u003ES1Q3T3 pattern, new right bundle branch block, right axis deviation\u003C/strong\u003E and/or T-wave inversion in leads v1-v4) are less common, and usually only seen in severe/large PEs (e.g. in PEs which cause haemodynamic instability). While S1Q3T3 is commonly taught as an association with PE, it is a very uncommon ECG finding.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENon-specific ST changes\u003C/strong\u003E are common and may be seen in any lead of the ECG. However these are less common with PE and more common with myocarditis and pericarditis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003Enormal ECG\u003C/strong\u003E may be seen in patients with a PE, however given that this patient has a heart rate of 120bpm, sinus tachycardia would be expected on her ECG.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Sinus tachycardia is the most common abnormality seen in 40% of PE cases."],"references":["Konstantinides S, Meyer G, Becattini C, Bueno H, Geersing G, Harjola V,  et al. 2019 ESC Guidelines for the diagnosis and management of acute pulmonary embolism developed in collaboration with the European Respiratory Society (ERS). European Respiratory Journal. 2019"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"39629"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1396"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"39629","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/39629"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-09-30T17:24:16+09:30","updatedAt":"2024-09-30T17:25:07+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1396"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"54157"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"2","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/2"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec0","name":"Cardiology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:47:21+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"11","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/11"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec1","name":"Respiratory Medicine","synonyms":["Pulmonology"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"t